This paper proposes a new generative framework for image modeling that focuses on the structure and style of images. The paper uses GANs to generate images and proposes a new approach that factors the image generation process into structure and style components. The paper also shows that the proposed model can be used to learn unsupervised RGBD representations. Given these factors, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are computer vision (cs.CV), graphics (cs.GR), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and multimedia (cs.MM).
